TITLE: Custom Presets Example React
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use custom color presets with the `ColorPicker` component.  A custom array of color values is defined and passed to the `presets` prop of the `ColorPicker`.  The `useState` hook is used to manage the selected color.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hxf31891/react-gradient-color-picker/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import React from 'react'
import ColorPicker from 'react-best-gradient-color-picker'

const customPresets = [
  'rgba(34, 164, 65, 1)',
  'rgba(210, 18, 40, .5)',
  'rgba(90, 110, 232, 1)',
  'rgba(65, 89, 56, 1)',
  'rgba(98, 189, 243, 1)',
  'rgba(255, 210, 198, 1)',
  'rgba(94, 94, 94, 1)'
] //max 18 colors, you can pass in more but the array will be sliced to the first 18

function MyApp() {
  const [color, setColor] = useState('rgba(255,255,255,1');

  return <ColorPicker value={color} onChange={setColor} presets={customPresets} />
}
```

