TITLE: Basic ColorPicker Example in React
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates a basic implementation of the ColorPicker component in a React application. It initializes a color state and uses the ColorPicker component to allow users to select a color, updating the state with the onChange prop.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hxf31891/react-gradient-color-picker/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import React from 'react'
import ColorPicker from 'react-best-gradient-color-picker'

function MyApp() {
  const [color, setColor] = useState('rgba(255,255,255,1)');

  return <ColorPicker value={color} onChange={setColor} />
}
```

