TITLE: Custom Locales Example React
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to customize the locales of the ColorPicker using the `locales` prop. It provides a custom object with translations for different parts of the ColorPicker component, for example translating `SOLID` and `GRADIENT`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/hxf31891/react-gradient-color-picker/blob/main/README.md#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import React from 'react'
import ColorPicker, { useColorPicker } from 'react-best-gradient-color-picker'

function MyApp() {
  const customLocales = {
    CONTROLS: {
      SOLID: 'Obiƒçne',
      GRADIENT: 'Gradijent',
    },
  }
  return (
    <div>
      <ColorPicker locales={customLocales} />
    </div>
  )
}
```

